    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The town’s roots stretch back to the late 1800s, when settlers were drawn by rich soil and a climate perfect for citrus farming.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.floridasmart.com/city-guide/alturas"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Citrus groves still dominate the landscape, and many families have farmed the land for generations, producing some of Florida’s best oranges.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        12,
        13
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
